//www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8ENX9UZ5\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀριστομένεος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀριστομένεος\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Ἀριστομένεος\">.ΡΙ...ΜΕΝΕ..\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"εἱμὶ\">.ΙΜΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"σᾶμα\">ΣΑΜΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Sansone in Cannata et al.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>I am the memorial of Aristomenes\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>A remarkable monumental rock-cut tomb deep in the hinterland of Akrai/Netum (suggested to fall within the territory of ancient Akrai), with a Greek name and archaic letter forms compatible with the Syracusan alphabet. Nothing remains within the tomb, whcih was presumably robbed out in antiquity (although Catagnino Berlinghieri et al. 2026 speculate on the (unlikely) possibility of the monument as cenotaph on that basis). The hypogeum shows signs of prehistoric presence/use also, and so the site has a long history of usage. Whether the deceased was Greek or 'hellenized' indigenous is impossible to know. The 'speaking' formula is attested elsewhere on the island, such as at Selinunte or Megara Hyblaea. The text shows Doric elements.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Sansone 2022 17-19, fig.13-14 \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castagnino Berlinghieri, Cannata, Ricciardi 2026 80-82, fig.22 \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Although difficult to read, the text appears to show both three-bar and four-bar sigma.\u003C/p> Line 1  60-130  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[168,171,174,177,180,183,186,189],{"id":169,"html":170},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8ENX9UZ5\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8ENX9UZ5\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀριστομένεος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀριστομένεος\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Ἀριστομένεος\">Ἀ̣ρισ̣τ̣ο̣μένεο̣ς̣\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"εἱμὶ\">ε̣ἱμὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"σᾶμα\">σᾶμα\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8ENX9UZ5\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8ENX9UZ5\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\