Identifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>contrada Arco\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository>in situ\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A rock cut tomb, with a doorway 1.07m wide by 0.86 m high, a worked facade 6.2m wide, and a rock-cut chamber behind 3.53m wide, 2.09m long and 1-1.08m high. The inscription is carved on the exterior in the space immediately above the doorway, with an epigraphic field c.177 cm wide.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.funerary_monument.rock-cut_tomb\" ref=\"http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300120624\">rock-cut tomb\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--Cannata et al.-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">177\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>The text is set out over a single line, become larger to the right\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Although difficult to read, the text appears to show both three-bar and four-bar sigma.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"60\" atMost=\"130\">60-130\u003C/height>\u003C!-- Cannata et al-->\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462068\">Acrae\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523922\">Palazzolo Acreide\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003Cgeo>37.05780, 14.89346\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0525\" notAfter-custom=\"-0475\" evidence=\"lettering textual-context\">Late 6th or early 5th century BCE (Sansone in Cannata et al. 2022)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"2022\">Found in 2022, in contrada Arco, which lies along the ancient route between Akrai and Netum (Noto antica), likely in the territory of ancient Akrai, c.8.5km SE of Palazzao and c.7km SW of Canicattini Bagni\u003Cgeo>37.0097335,14.9831142\u003C/geo>\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- location of the tomb based upon Cannata et al. fig.3 -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">none\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n               \u003Cchange when=\"2026-03-05\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created draft file from published materials\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\u003Csurface/>\u003C!-- \n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001900_tiled.tif\" height=\"5520px\" width=\"3680px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-13\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001900.jpg\" height=\"5520px\" width=\"3680px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2015-01-13\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface> -->\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\" source=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/8ENX9UZ5\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cw>\u003Cunclear>Ἀ\u003C/unclear>ρι\u003Cunclear>στο\u003C/unclear>μένε\u003Cunclear>ος\u003C/unclear>\u003C/w>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cw>\u003Cunclear>ε\u003C/unclear>ἱμὶ\u003C/w> \u003Cw>σᾶμα\u003C/w>\n                 \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text of Sansone in Cannata et al.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>I am the memorial of Aristomenes\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>A remarkable monumental rock-cut tomb deep in the hinterland of Akrai/Netum (suggested to fall within the territory of ancient Akrai), with a Greek name and archaic letter forms compatible with the Syracusan alphabet. Nothing remains within the tomb, whcih was presumably robbed out in antiquity (although Catagnino Berlinghieri et al. 2026 speculate on the (unlikely) possibility of the monument as cenotaph on that basis). The hypogeum shows signs of prehistoric presence/use also, and so the site has a long history of usage. Whether the deceased was Greek or 'hellenized' indigenous is impossible to know. The 'speaking' formula is attested elsewhere on the island, such as at Selinunte or Megara Hyblaea. The text shows Doric elements.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Sansone\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2022\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>17-19, fig.13-14\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/IWTBCB32\"/>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Castagnino Berlinghieri, Cannata, Ricciardi\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2026\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>80-82, fig.22\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/PKPAES83\"/>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
